ed or inappropriate. Yet the idea that some things are wrong beyond toleration still has significant currency. If 'evil' can capture that significance, it merits a closer look.Key FeaturesPresents a broad ranging exploration of the idea of evil in contemporary theoryOffers a philosophical analysis of the role of evil in ethicsAnalyses the idea of evil in classic arguments  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2022) 0aGood and evil -- Political aspects. 0aGood and evilxPolitical aspects. 0aPolitical science -- Philosophy. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 4aPolitics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBoucher, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBudde, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarrard, Eve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaddock, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorton, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilbank, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoberts, Peri, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRoberts, Peri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShorten, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSutch, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSutch, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748654123zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748654123423Co